/use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531053\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2531053\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 14, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104psh1665702538803.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/psh1665702538803.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/psh1665702538803.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"psh1665702538803\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The <span class=\"keyword apiname\">uniface.SyntaxError</span> object provides access to the error number\n    and message of a field syntax error, and to the incorrect field value that caused the\n    error.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"psh1665702538803__section_y4j_w2c_dwb\">\n<p class=\"p\"><span class=\"keyword apiname\">uniface.SyntaxError</span> is returned by the <span class=\"keyword apiname\">Field.getError</span>\n        function when used in the OnSyntaxError and OnSyntaxErrorResolved web triggers. </p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"psh1665702538803__section_nls_2fc_dwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d142846e63\">Syntax Error Properties</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"psh1665702538803__table_d15248e1_d15249e1_d15250e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"psh1665702538803__table_d15248e1_d15249e1_d15250e1__entry__1\"> Property Name </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"psh1665702538803__table_d15248e1_d15249e1_d15250e1__entry__2\"> Description </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"psh1665702538803__table_d15248e1_d15249e1_d15250e1__entry__1\"> exceptionCode </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"psh1665702538803__table_d15248e1_d15249e1_d15250e1__entry__2\"> Syntax error code. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"psh1665702538803__table_d15248e1_d15249e1_d15250e1__entry__1\"> message </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"psh1665702538803__table_d15248e1_d15249e1_d15250e1__entry__2\"> Syntax error message. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"psh1665702538803__table_d15248e1_d15249e1_d15250e1__entry__1\"> valueInError </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"psh1665702538803__table_d15248e1_d15249e1_d15250e1__entry__2\"> Field value that caused the syntax error. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"psh1665702538803__section_r3l_hfc_dwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d142846e121\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"psh1665702538803__p_d127598e1_d127599e1_d127600e1\">A <span class=\"keyword apiname\">uniface.SyntaxError</span> object is\n        generated when:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"psh1665702538803__ul_pyq_jfc_dwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"psh1665702538803__li_d46280e1_d46281e1_d46282e1\">The user makes a syntax error in a field, which\n          causes the OnSyntaxError web trigger to be fired. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"psh1665702538803__li_d46283e1_d46284e1_d46285e1\">The user corrects an error, which causes the\n          OnSyntaxErrorResolved web trigger to be fired. </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"psh1665702538803__p_d127601e1_d127602e1_d127603e1\">In these triggers, you can access the properties of\n        the <span class=\"keyword apiname\">uniface.SyntaxError</span> error object using the\n          <span class=\"keyword apiname\">getError</span> function of the field. </p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"psh1665702538803__section_ggh_rtv_1dc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d142846e151\">Example: Using uniface.SyntaxError</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"psh1665702538803__p_d127607e1_d127608e1_d127609e1\">For example, in the following code, the OnSyntaxError\n        web trigger is used to display an alert box with the information about the error and the\n        field it applies to. This trigger is activated when the browser detects a syntax error.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">The example performs the following:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\" id=\"psh1665702538803__ol_nss_sfc_dwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"psh1665702538803__li_d46286e1_d46287e1_d46288e1\">Declares a variable called <code class=\"ph codeph\">vError</code>\n          and assigns a value that contains the error information, assembled using the functions of\n          the <span class=\"keyword apiname\">uniface.Field</span> object. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"psh1665702538803__li_d46289e1_d46290e1_d46291e1\">Displays an alert with contents of the\n            <code class=\"ph codeph\">vError</code> variable. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"psh1665702538803__li_d46292e1_d46293e1_d46294e1\">Returns <code class=\"ph codeph\">true</code> to enable the default\n          Uniface error handling, which puts a red border around the field. </li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104psh1665702538803_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"psh1665702538803__codeblock_u11_tfc_dwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">webtrigger OnSyntaxError\nscope\n input\nendscope\njavascript\n //; this = the current field\n var vError = 'Error: ' + this.getError().exceptionCode + this.getError().message + '/n'; <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#psh1665702538803__li_d46286e1_d46287e1_d46288e1\">1</a>\n vError += 'in field ' + this.getLabel().getValue() + './n'\n vError += 'The incorrect value is: ' this.getError().valueInError;\n alert(vError); <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#psh1665702538803__li_d46289e1_d46290e1_d46291e1\">2</a>\n return true    <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#psh1665702538803__li_d46292e1_d46293e1_d46294e1\">3</a>\nendjavascript</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zkz1665702538660.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>getError()</a><p>Returns an error object for the field, if a syntax error or validation error occurred.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aqh1665702590886.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Syntax Checking in Dynamic Server Pages</a><p>Uniface always performs server-side syntax checks when data in a dynamic server page (DSP) is validated or stored. It is also possible to perform browser-side syntax checks, so that errors are flagged before incorrect data is submitted to the server.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dcx1665702590735.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>webtrigger onSyntaxError</a><p>The onSyntaxError web trigger is activated when a field syntax violation is detected in the browser. It can be used to customize or override the default syntax error handling.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uuy1665702590810.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>webtrigger onSyntaxErrorResolved</a><p>The onSyntaxErrorResolved web trigger is used to customize behavior when a field syntax error has been corrected.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531053\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531053\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "uniface.SyntaxError Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 The uniface.SyntaxError object provides access to the error number and message of a field syntax error, and to the incorrect field value that caused the error. uniface.SyntaxError is returned by the Field.getError function when used in the OnSyntaxError and OnSyntaxErrorResolved web triggers. Syntax Error Properties Property Name Description exceptionCode Syntax error code. message Syntax error message. valueInError Field value that caused the syntax error. Description A uniface.SyntaxError object is generated when: The user makes a syntax error in a field, which causes the OnSyntaxError web trigger to be fired. The user corrects an error, which causes the OnSyntaxErrorResolved web trigger to be fired. In these triggers, you can access the properties of the uniface.SyntaxError error object using the getError function of the field. Example: Using uniface.SyntaxError For example, in the following code, the OnSyntaxError web trigger is used to display an alert box with the information about the error and the field it applies to. This trigger is activated when the browser detects a syntax error. The example performs the following: Declares a variable called vError and assigns a value that contains the error information, assembled using the functions of the uniface.Field object. Displays an alert with contents of the vError variable. Returns true to enable the default Uniface error handling, which puts a red border around the field. Explain this code webtrigger OnSyntaxError scope input endscope javascript //; this = the current field var vError = 'Error: ' + this.getError().exceptionCode + this.getError().message + '/n'; 1 vError += 'in field ' + this.getLabel().getValue() + './n' vError += 'The incorrect value is: ' this.getError().valueInError; alert(vError); 2 return true 3 endjavascript Copy Related Links getError() Returns an error object for the field, if a syntax error or validation error occurred. Syntax Checking in Dynamic Server Pages Uniface always performs server-side syntax checks when data in a dynamic server page (DSP) is validated or stored. It is also possible to perform browser-side syntax checks, so that errors are flagged before incorrect data is submitted to the server. webtrigger onSyntaxError The onSyntaxError web trigger is activated when a field syntax violation is detected in the browser. It can be used to customize or override the default syntax error handling. webtrigger onSyntaxErrorResolved The onSyntaxErrorResolved web trigger is used to customize behavior when a field syntax error has been corrected. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}